{
  "stem": "9963.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because that took people from all the camps, you know, what they had to evacuate because the Allied soldiers on the way were closing up, you know, and they didn't want to leave us, you know, for them.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So they-- they put us on a train, and the train had to go from there to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But the train was standing for days on the side, and we were in open wagons.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Again, we didn't have nothing what to eat for days, for weeks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The train was-- I don't-- can't imagine how long it took, you know, the train to go from one place to another, till we came to Gleiwitz.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It stayed there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, the thing is, what I failed to tell you, it was so crowded in that train, if somebody sit down on the train, couldn't get up anymore-- was trampled to death.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as-- so you're standing up for days in and days out, days and nights.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You're getting tired.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You have no choice.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You're falling down.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it's good that I had friends, you know, what that took me, put me in a corner, and they stand around, you know, make like a fence that nobody will step on me.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I could rest a few hours.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Later somebody else sit down, and with-- and so that way, what we changed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What we saved our lives for each other.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was just unbearable to stand for so many hours, so many days-- and without food.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, it is understandable that people falling down.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If you fall down-- you know the-- he didn't get up anymore.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was nobody's fault, because we were so tight, but we could not help it.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
